quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,101,"And how do you disbelieve while it is to you that the verses of Allah are recited, and present amidst you is His Messenger? And whoever holds on to Allah, he is surely guided to the straight path."
  3,102,"0 those who believe, fear Allah, a fear which is His due, and let not yourself die save as Muslims."
  3,103,"And hold on to the cord of Allah, all of you, and be not divided. And remember the blessing of Allah upon you: When you were enemies to each other, and He brought your hearts together, then you, with His grace, became brothers. And you were at the brink of a pit of Fire, then, He saved you from it. This is how Allah makes His signs clear to you, so that you may take the right path."
  3,104,"And there has to be a group of people from among you who call towards the good, and bid the Fair and forbid the Unfair. And it is these who are successful."
  3,105,"And do not be like those who became divided and fell into disputes after the clear signs had come to them. And for them there is grave punishment."
  3,106,"On a day when faces shall turn bright and faces shall turn dark, as for those whose faces turn dark, (they shall be questioned): 'Did you disbelieve after you had accepted the Faith? Now taste the punishment because you have been disbelieving.""
  3,107,"And as for those whose faces turn bright, they rest in Allah's mercy. They are there forever."
  3,108,"These are the verses of Allah We recite to you with all veracity. And Allah wants no injustice for (anyone in) the worlds."